  "original_title": "\u0d86\u0dbb\u0dca.\u0d91\u0db8\u0dca.\u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0d91\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1-\u0dc0\u0dda\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "It is not mandatory to reserve a date and time to come to RMV",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Motor Transport Commissioner General Nishantha Weerasinghe told 'Lankadeepa' today (16) that it is not mandatory to book a date and time to get services from the Motor Transport Department and people who come to get services from the Motor Transport Department will get service even if they do not book a date and time.",
        "The Motor Commissioner General who said that people who want to book a date and time can get that service, also mentioned that he instructed the department not to send any person who comes to get the service through again.",
        "Nishantha Weerasinghe said that the officials of all the offices of the Motor Transport Department have been informed to come to work on five days of the week and this decision was reached based on the complaints received that some people who booked a date and time have to face many problems.",
        "Mr. Weerasinghe further said that the method of booking a date and time was introduced focusing on various difficulties due to the spread of the 'Covid' virus and that these difficulties have now been overcome and people will be more comfortable as a large number of people resort to booking dates and times."
      ],
